google.subtitle: The Dark Room
google.description: His drive to preserve their beauty for eternity cannot be controlled Derrick, now David, tried to suppress the bad place within himself—the part that wanted to punish the girls who had shunned him. He knew he was good at his work—his actual photography—and he tried to make that more important than the darkness inside. But it was no use. His mission was to immortalize the beauty of young women—and nothing would stop him. Senior Vicki Valentine is devastated by the loss of her best friend, SueAnne, unable to believe that someone would actually murder her. Spending time with the new guy in town, Scott, helps, but she can’t shake the feeling that something else is about to happen. Little does she know that David has been preparing his next photo shoot already . . . with her.
google.title: The Photographer II
